example setup for a basic recognition using the CMU Census corpus

contents:
 * input
    - corpus files (transcription files converted to BLISS format)
    - lexicon (pronunciation dictionary converted to BLISS format)

 * tools
    - converter scripts

 * training
    - acoustic front end: MFCC features + derivatives
    - acoustic model training of monophone models
    - estimation of phonetic decision tree (CART)
    - estimation of LDA
    - acoustic model training of triphone models

 * recognition
    - decoding using monophone/triphone models 
    - no usage of a language model (zerogram LM)

